Back in April 2019, I was bored at work, my brain was atrophying, and I was=
 at best a passive participant in the Great Online Game. Then I saw a tweet=
 from David Perell about a course he was running, Write of Passage. I loved=
 writing and I was bored, so I decided to take a flyer.
Two years later, I can trace every good thing that=E2=80=99s happened to me=
 professionally -- this newsletter, Not Boring Capital, friendships with gr=
eat people --=C2=A0 back to that course. Over the next couple of weeks, I=
=E2=80=99m going to go in-depth on my writing journey, leading up to a live=
 workshop with David on August 11th. Over 4 short essays, I=E2=80=99ll tell=
 you about:
How to start writing online, even if you think you have nothing to write ab=
out.=C2=A0
The messy process I use to write way too many words every week.
How to build your Personal Monopoly and attract serendipity online=E2=80=A6=
 in other words, how to get involved in the Great Online Game.
I can=E2=80=99t recommend the course highly enough=E2=80=A6 but I=E2=80=99l=
l try. Sign up here to receive four emails from me and learn what writing o=
nline can do for you.=C2=A0
