ior. And Lei had the medals to back up his world-class brilliance.
In 1996, the 17-year-old Lei won Gold at the International Olympiad in Info=
rmatics in Hungary, and he came back the next year and grabbed a Bronze. He=
 attended Tsinghua University, widely recognized as the best Chinese univer=
sity, and afterwards obtained a PhD from the University of Wisconsin-Madiso=
n, like Huang.=C2=A0
Source: KrAsia [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM1qwzAQhJ_GOhpJK8fSQY=
dCyaGU0lN7NPpZJyK2FCQ5wW9fOz4Ull3YYRjmc6biJeVV31OpZF9DXe-oIz7LhLViJkvBPASv2=
YlL6IQiXgvPZCdJKMOYEWcTJl3zguS-2Ck4U0OKLwelvCNXPQoEC6ZjvRidAcmoAuk5WNmh4mw8=
cs3iA0aHGh-Y1xSRTPpa67008Nbw8zbP57Nd01IXi61L8_4x1V0bOD8aeP_4Ll-_3n6aH0GC5pQ=
z2vMT413HZMtaxSVlwiluRk9P3PYOGFAPo3Bwcko2gs4X3pbFlmrcbQ8gWcdUbcohXjb5djUzTi=
9hKzpsd15iqOuA0dgJ_cGgHihfVIYLRswbYj-YugPsgQrGVQ_d0XmDBIopUL0iW7JPmyv-h_4Bp=
FGJRg]
Lei attended Wisconsin a few years before Huang, so the two didn=E2=80=99t =
meet there, but after stints at Google (like Huang), Yahoo!, and IBM, Lei m=
oved back to China in 2007 to work at Huang=E2=80=99s first startup: ouku.c=
om. The duo has worked together ever since.=C2=A0
In 2011, Lei went to work for Huang=E2=80=99s online gaming company, Xinyou=
di Studio, as CTO. Four years later, Huang got the band back together at Pi=
nhaohuo, a DTC fruit company that was the predecessor to Pinduoduo. Lei was=
 a member of the founding team in 2015, and was promoted to CTO in 2016.=C2=
=A0
Pinhaohuo lasted only a year as a standalone company, but it did two things=
 that would contribute to Pinduoduo=E2=80=99s eventual success: WeChat and =
Logistics.
WeChat is China=E2=80=99s most popular messaging app. Today, its 1.2 billio=
n users spend more time on WeChat than Americans spend on all social media =
apps combined. It=E2=80=99s a huge firehose of traffic... that the incumben=
t Alibaba couldn=E2=80=99t touch. WeChat is owned by Alibaba=E2=80=99s riva=
l, Tencent, and as Turner points out [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxV=
kMtuxCAMRb9m2E3EIy8WLLrpb0QEnAwqgYiYVvn7OpNFVclgydbV9T3OIqy5nGbPB7Lrm_DcwST=
4OSIgQmH1gDIFb0QvR9W1mnnTejF2IwvHtBSAzYZosFRge51jcBZDTm8F57JjL7MI3go9aGe909=
7LYehAz6OnKde27W9fW32A5MDAN5QzJ2DRvBD346E-HvKTCmtJUJqjzgda99W4vNF0v15Ivmaqp=
03-SXqkM2I8nyFRvkIhPQtGcin4IHshu06MjWi0HLlonZZ28byX8-CUUNyrpXWqd3p8tHxb5T9D=
VkzKOOcS0krrr5fdIL4XFH6ivtUU8Jwg2TmCv7ngjfdNalqBQlwXTRYvqIMiDlIPqrs5EDilhVY=
EjJGzz6RKf6a_6q2Saw]:
Pinduoduo=E2=80=99s primary competitor today, Alibaba, had also banned its =
sellers from using both WeChat and WeChat Pay. Its biggest incumbent compet=
itor was un-incentivized to react to this newfound distribution channel.
Hamilton Helmer fans will recognize that as one of the 7 Powers: counter-po=
sitioning. It worked beautifully. By September 2015, Pinhaohuo was the #1 f=
ree app in China, and handled over 100k orders per day, facilitated by its =
use of WeChat=E2=80=99s WeChat Pay, which made small transactions frictionl=
ess and affordable.=C2=A0
The influx of demand for extremely perishable items (fruit) also forced Pin=
haohuo to beef up its logistics. According to Turner, a surge in demand for=
 lychees led Pinhaohuo to add 100 new ops employees, open six new warehouse=
s, and reduce turnaround times dramatically. =E2=80=9CWithin a month, most =
fruit spent only a few hours in any of PHH=E2=80=99s six fulfillment center=
s,=E2=80=9D Turner wrote. =E2=80=9CThe time from farm-to-table was often no=
 more than two or three days.=E2=80=9D
Pinhaohuo also opened up their logistics beyond early partner SF Express (f=
ounded by Huang=E2=80=99s friend and investor, Wang Wei) in order to meet g=
rowing demand, and built features that let couriers bid for orders in real-=
time. They both tapped into China=E2=80=99s robust and affordable local log=
istics network, and built software to wrangle some of the chaos.=C2=A0
When Huang merged Pinhaohuo with his gaming-commerce company, Pinduoduo, in=
 2016, the combined company had tens of millions of users, gaming DNA, and =
the logistics backbone to fulfill all of the demand that might create. Pind=
uoduo means =E2=80=9CTogether, More Savings, More Fun;=E2=80=9D the name li=
terally described exactly the combination the company was going for.=C2=A0
That combination -- dubbed =E2=80=9Csocial commerce=E2=80=9D -- was a revel=
ation that took the market by storm. When Pinduoduo entered the Chinese eco=
mmerce race in earnest in 2016, the market was already full. You had Alibab=
a in first place with Taobao and Tmall, Tencent-backed JD comfortably in se=
cond, and no room for a serious third place contender... until Pinduoduo ma=
de room with some good old fashioned low-end disruption.=C2=A0
Pinduoduo realized that there was an enormous swath of customers who were e=
ither overserved or completely unserved by China=E2=80=99s existing ecommer=
ce platforms. Specifically, while Taobao and JD served first and second-tie=
r cities, those with populations over 3 million people and the bulk of the =
country=E2=80=99s GDP, there was no affordable option for people in third-t=
ier cities and below, who made up the vast majority of China=E2=80=99s popu=
lation.=C2=A0
Source: Asia Briefing [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkU2OhSAQhE_z2Gn=
4UYEFi9nMNQw2rZKnaADHePvB5ySTdOhFUanK12AzTlu8zL6lTO6nz9eOJuCZFswZIzkSxt47wz=
quRNto4kzjmGoV8akfI-Jq_WJyPJDsx7B4sNlv4eOglLdkNrwF6SRFCpxZQCaFAjEMo6KjtSPAk=
2sP5zEAGvzBeG0ByWLmnPf0El8v_l3mPM8aZh9sNUSPow9TDdtahLttWR8tVeDzVWWPsYLFpuTH=
v0qVuz3oyk_iDaecUck7xtuWqZrVmivKGtDcjo52fJAgmKBOjA2IDrR6NXSdeJ2OIWUL7zuaRBO=
2PGyxVCnye7YrLh-hkOjLXo9QyvQY7LCgeyDlh_UHWz9hwFhu4Hqbb8JS0IZxLUX7QCkUhWZaaK=
lJSXZbcYX_0F9_DZdv]
People in these cities had less money but more time. Many had never shopped=
 online, but they did use WeChat. While price is always a strong attack vec=
tor, it was a particularly strong attack vector when trying to reach these =
previously unserved groups. With more time on their hands than their fellow=
 citizens in cities like Shanghai and Beijing, these buyers were willing to=
 do things like, say, play games and tell their friends to buy with them in=
 exchange for discounts.=C2=A0
Starting at the low-end of the market forced Huang, Lei, and team to comple=
tely rethink what a mobile-first ecommerce app should look like and priorit=
ize. The result is Pinduoduo.=C2=A0
To learn what Pinduoduo does, whether and how its model could work in the w=
est, recent developments at the company, the Bull and Bear cases, and PDD=
=E2=80=99s Metaverse potential (you didn=E2=80=99t think I=E2=80=99d write =
a piece without mentioning the Metaverse, right?):
