 modest $71. The write-ups and podcasts slowed to a trickle. We&#8217;d acc=
limated to the awe. Nothing shocked us anymore, not even a business that <s=
trong>doubled revenue to $4.3B in 2019</strong><em><strong>as a five-year-o=
ld company</strong></em>.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">And then it RIPPED. As growth stocks =
around the world flew, PDD flew further and faster, rising as high as $212 =
per share in mid-February, good for a <strong>market cap north of $250 bill=
ion.</strong></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: =
26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Since then, due to a mix of China fear, the depar=
ture of its founder Chairman, and reversion to the mean, PDD has <strong>fa=
llen over 50%</strong>, back down to where it stands today, a nice, palindr=
omic <strong>$96.69 per share for a market cap of $122 billion.&nbsp;</stro=
ng></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 1em 0;">It&#8217;s been a bumpy ride. Where&#8217;s it all going to=
 shake out?&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-heig=
ht: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Would PDD&#8217;s $250B fall market cap still=
 stand absent regulatory concerns? Or is PDD still overvalued at $122B? Is =
it just kind of just like a Groupon for fruit? Groupon grew quickly too... =
before it fell just as fast.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Whether you&#8217;re a bull or a b=
ear, Pinduoduo is an absolutely fascinating company that has created, remix=
ed, and popularized key innovations like team buying, &#8220;Interactive Ec=
ommerce,&#8221; and Consumer-to-Manufacturer (C2M). Fans argue that PDD bro=
ught the shopping mall to customers&#8217; phones for the first time. No on=
e can argue that its ascent from $0 to nearly $10 billion in revenue has be=
en anything short of spectacular. In the bullest of bull cases, it even has=
 a shot at powering commerce in the Metaverse, backed by its largest outsid=
e shareholder and Metaverse-kingmaker, Tencent.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">But quest=
ions remain. Under &#8220;new&#8221; leadership, will Pinduoduo continue to=
 innovate, or will it slowly blend into the Chinese ecommerce landscape as =
it steals features from its bigger rivals, and they do the same to it?&nbsp=
;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0 0 1em 0;">Today, we&#8217;re going to explore PDD&#8217;s last year bef=
ore debating whether its stock is a buy or sell. (Of course, this is for en=
